      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:6:8:17:2",
      "text": [
        " أَوَّلُ مَنِ اتَّخَذَ النَّعْلَيْنِ إِبْرَاهِيمُ ( عليه السلام ) ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Al Nowfaly, from Al Sakuny, ",
          "Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> has said: ‘The first one to take to the sandals was Ibrahim<sup>asws</sup>’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "2. Ali ibn Ibrahim has narrated from his father from al-Nawfaliy from al-Sakuniy who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said, ‘The first one who used footgear was Ibrahim ‘Alayhi al- Salam.”’ "
        ]
      }
